<br>
Those that fear kite walk around slowly hacking the backs of mobs up, but are pretty harmless and unobtrusive.<br>
<br>
Those that chant kite cover a good bit of ground, but as long as they're careful, there's no reason for anyone to get hurt.  The kill rate is fair for this type of soloing, but it's rarely a problem to have a chant kiter hogging too many spawns.<br>
<br>
Charm kiting, and especially swarm kiting is more risky, and harder to do right.  If done right, however, it's great experience (until you hit a lag spike, or charm the wrong mob, in which case you're toast).  This kind of kiting should be done away from others, and other people should be very careful about stepping in on a swarm kiting bard;  It's very low-aggro kiting, so you could easily get the whole swarm on you if you're not careful.<br>
<br>
Bottom line: There are bards who hog spawns, much like druids, and, dare I say it, wizards, who quad kite constantly with KEI.  It's not the class, it's the individuals that are jerks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mirdorr>mirdorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/18/03 9:37:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25537.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I agree!</span><hr size=1> I was glad to hear that one or two of you have tried the bard/wizard duo thing.  I hope to attempt that in the near future, and I've been thinking about several different strategies.   <br>
